   2002 Ag Outlook Forum:
   Securing Global Markets
   January 30, 2002 -- The 2002 Ag Outlook Conference, which features a
   keynote address from Secretary Veneman, will spotlight 2002 farm
   prospects, trade and agricultural policy, and international acceptance
   of biotech crops. Part of this year's program will be webcast. The
   conference will be held February 21-22 in Arlington, VA.
   To register: Online | Print form
   More
     __________________________________________________________________

   Mail Delay
   January 17, 2002 -- Incoming first-class mail to RMA received between
   Oct. 1 and Nov. 14, 2001, beginning with zip codes 202-205 has been
   destroyed due to possible anthrax contamination. If you sent us
   first-class mail during that time, please resend it. Time-sensitive
   mail should be sent using other mail delivery services or by fax or
   e-mail. First-class mail is being delayed a month or more because it
   must be irradiated off-site. Thank you for your patience.
     __________________________________________________________________

   Price Election Flexibility for 2002 Spring Crops
   January 16, 2002 -- RMA announced that it would provide additional
   flexibility to producers on price elections due to ongoing farm bill
   deliberations.
   More
     __________________________________________________________________

   Written Agreements Reaffirmed
   January 16, 2002 -- RMA will continue to process written agreements for
   the 2002 crop year. Changes are likely for the 2003 crop year.
   More
     __________________________________________________________________

   We Need Your Input
   January 18, 2002 -- RMA is requesting input from vegetable/flower, lawn
   seed, and sesame producers to increase participation by underserved
   producers in the Federal crop insurance program. The input is critical
   in determining the need and direction of future research and
   development.
   Vegetable/Flower Seed (PDF file) | Lawn Seed (PDF file) | Sesame (PDF
   file)
     __________________________________________________________________

   Actuary Needed
   January 11, 2002 -- This challenging, non-supervisory position allows
   you to do unique, cutting-edge work. It offers the right candidate a
   competitive salary plus a possible one-time bonus, good benefits, and
   relocation assistance. The application deadline is February 20, 2002.
   More
     __________________________________________________________________

   New Sheriff in Town
   January 11, 2002 -- Robert Crockett, RMA's new Sanctions Officer, is an
   old hand at crop insurance who will be applying new sanctions to those
   who abuse the crop insurance program.
   More
     __________________________________________________________________

   Crime Means Time
   December 27, 2001 -- A North Texas man and his wife, a crop insurance
   agent, are going to prison and paying fines and restitution for filing
   fictitious crop insurance claims and related charges.
   h More
   Related item: Press release (PDF file)

                                Weather Watch
                              January 30, 2002

   DAILY SPOTLIGHT ON:
   The West -- Beneficial precipitation is falling across portions of
   Arizona and New Mexico, boosting soil moisture reserves and
   high-elevation snow packs. Meanwhile, cool weather in California is
   slowing winter grain development, although citrus trees and fruit
   continue to escape injury.

